{"award_age":52.0,"bio_image":"full\/357cd9d36139e12989acdf863c136832a5d4b6e9.jpg","category":"Chemistry","country":"Germany","date_of_birth":"1876-12-25T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"1959-06-09T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/7\/79\/Windaus.jpg\/180px-Windaus.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Adolf_Otto_Reinhold_Windaus","mini_bio":"<p><b>Adolf Otto Reinhold Windaus<\/b> (25 December 1876 \u2013 9 June 1959) was a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Germany\" title=\"Germany\">German<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemist\" title=\"Chemist\">chemist<\/a> who won a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry<\/a> in 1928 for his work on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sterol\" title=\"Sterol\">sterols<\/a> and their relation to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vitamin\" title=\"Vitamin\">vitamins<\/a>. He was the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doctoral_advisor\" title=\"Doctoral advisor\">doctoral advisor<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Adolf_Butenandt\" title=\"Adolf Butenandt\">Adolf Butenandt<\/a> who also won a Nobel Prize in Chemistry in 1939.<\/p><p>Adolf Windaus was born in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Berlin\" title=\"Berlin\">Berlin<\/a>. His interest in chemistry was raised by lectures of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hermann_Emil_Fischer\" title=\"Hermann Emil Fischer\">Emil Fischer<\/a>. He started studying medicine and chemistry in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Humboldt_University_of_Berlin\" title=\"Humboldt University of Berlin\">Berlin<\/a> and later in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Freiburg\" title=\"University of Freiburg\">Freiburg<\/a>. He got his PhD in early 1900 and focused on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cholesterol\" title=\"Cholesterol\">cholesterol<\/a> and other <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sterol\" title=\"Sterol\">sterols<\/a> at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Freiburg\" title=\"University of Freiburg\">University of Freiburg<\/a>. In 1913 he became professor for chemistry at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Innsbruck\" title=\"University of Innsbruck\">University of Innsbruck<\/a><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> and in 1915 he changed to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_G%C3%B6ttingen\" title=\"University of G\u00f6ttingen\">University of G\u00f6ttingen<\/a><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup> where he stayed until his retirement in 1944<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Timefact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Timeline_Tracer\/Chronology_source_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Timeline Tracer\/Chronology source needed\"><span title=\"This chronology\/history reference needs citation to reliable sources (September 2011)\">chronology citation needed<\/span><\/a><\/i>]<\/sup>.<\/p><p>He was involved in the discovery of the transformation of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cholesterol\" title=\"Cholesterol\">cholesterol<\/a> through several steps to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cholecalciferol\" title=\"Cholecalciferol\">vitamin D<sub>3<\/sub><\/a> (Cholecalciferol). He gave his patents to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Merck_KGaA\" title=\"Merck KGaA\">Merck<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bayer\" title=\"Bayer\">Bayer<\/a> and they brought out the medical <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vigantol\" title=\"Vigantol\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Vigantol<\/a> in 1927.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Adolf_Otto_Reinhold_Windaus#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Adolf Otto Reinhold Windaus","place_of_birth":"Berlin ,  Germany","place_of_death":"G\u00f6ttingen ,  Germany","text":"Adolf Otto Reinhold Windaus , Chemistry, 1928","year":1928.0}